{"review": [{"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 0, "sentence": "This is a paper of the verification of neural networks, i.e. check their robustness,"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 1, "sentence": "and the main contribution here is to tackle it as a statistical problem adressed with"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 2, "sentence": "multi-level splitting Monte Carlo approach."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 3, "sentence": "I found the paper well motivated and original,"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 4, "sentence": "resulting in a publishable piece of research up to a few necessary adjustments."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 5, "sentence": "These"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 6, "sentence": "concern principally notation issues and some potential improvements in the writing."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 7, "sentence": "Let me list below some main remarks along the text, including also some typos."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 8, "sentence": "* In the introduction, \"the classical approach\" is mentioned but to be the latter is"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 9, "sentence": "insufficiently covered. Some more detail would be welcome."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 10, "sentence": "* page 2, \"predict the probability\": rather employ \"estimate\" in such context?"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 11, "sentence": "* \"linear piecewise\": \"piecewise linear\"?"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 12, "sentence": "* what is \"an exact upper bound\"?"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 13, "sentence": "* In related work, no reference to previous work on \"statistical\" approaches to NN"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 14, "sentence": "verification. Is it actually the case that this angle has never been explored so far?"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 15, "sentence": "* I am not an expert but to me \"the density of adversarial examples\" calls for further"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 16, "sentence": "explanation."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 17, "sentence": "* From page 3 onwards: I was truly confused by the use of [x] throughought the text"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 18, "sentence": "(e.g. in Equation (4))"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 19, "sentence": "."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 20, "sentence": "x is already present within the indicator, no need to add yet"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 21, "sentence": "another instance of it. Here and later I suffered from what seems to be like an awkward"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 22, "sentence": "attempts to stress dependency on variables that already appear or should otherwise"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 23, "sentence": "appear in a less convoluted way."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 24, "sentence": "* In Section 4, it took me some time to understand that the considered metrics do not"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 25, "sentence": "require actual observations but rather concern coherence properties of the NN per se."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 26, "sentence": "While this follows from the current framework, the paper might benefit from some more"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 27, "sentence": "explanation in words regarding this important aspect."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 28, "sentence": "* In page 6, what is meant by \"more perceptually similar to the datapoint\"?"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 29, "sentence": "* In the discussion: is it really \"a new measure\" that is introduced here?"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 30, "sentence": "*"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 31, "sentence": "In the appendix: the MH acronym should better be introduced, as should the notation"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 32, "sentence": "g(x,|x')"}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 33, "sentence": "if not done elsewhere (in which case a cross-reference would be welcome)."}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 34, "sentence": "Besides this, writing \"the last samples\" requires disambiguation (using \"respective\"?)."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 3, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Motivation/Impact", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 4, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Motivation/Impact", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 5, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [{"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 6, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 7, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 8, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 9, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_