", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 21, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 22, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 23, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 24, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 25, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 26, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 27, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 28, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 29, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Clarification", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 30, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Clarification", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 31, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 32, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 33, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": true}, {"text_id": "HkxcI2vu37", "sid": 34, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}], "rebuttal": [{"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 0, "sentence": "We are glad you found our work interesting and novel, and thank you for your helpful suggestions for improving the writing. We have taken them on board in the revised paper, making a number of edits."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 1, "sentence": "1. \"In the introduction, \"the classical approach\" is mentioned but to be the latter is"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 2, "sentence": "insufficiently covered. Some more detail would be welcome.\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 3, "sentence": "We have added a reference to what we mean by the classical approach in the related works section."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 4, "sentence": "2. \"page 2, \"predict the probability\": rather employ \"estimate\" in such context?\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 5, "sentence": "We have changed \u201cpredict\u201d to \u201cestimate\u201d."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 6, "sentence": "3. \"'linear piecewise': 'piecewise linear'?\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 7, "sentence": "This was a typo and we have corrected this phrase."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 8, "sentence": "4. \"What is 'an exact upper bound'?\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 9, "sentence": "We mean that it is a true upper bound instead of just being a stochastic estimate of an upper bound (while, on the other hand, Weng et al\u2019s approach is stochastic estimate of a lower bound)."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 10, "sentence": "However, we agree that the \u201cexact\u201d is superfluous and have removed it."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 11, "sentence": "5. \"I am not an expert but to me 'the density of adversarial examples' calls for further"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 12, "sentence": "explanation.\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 13, "sentence": "We think perhaps \u201cthe prevalence of adversarial examples\u201d would be a better phrase and have corrected this."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 14, "sentence": "We mean that the input model density is integrated over for our metric to calculate the volume of counterexamples in a subset of the input domain, relative the overall volume of that input domain."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 15, "sentence": "6. \"From page 3 onwards: I was truly confused by the use of [x] throughout the text"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 16, "sentence": "(e.g. in Equation (4))"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 17, "sentence": "."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 18, "sentence": "x is already present within the indicator, no need to add yet"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 19, "sentence": "another instance of it.\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 20, "sentence": "In retrospect, we agree that this was confusing and have removed the [x] notation from the indicator function."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 21, "sentence": "7. \"In related work, no reference to previous work on \"statistical\" approaches to NN"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 22, "sentence": "verification. Is it actually the case that this angle has never been explored so far?\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 23, "sentence": "As far as we are aware this is correct: we have not been able to find any prior work which aims to estimate the statistical prevalence of counterexamples."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 24, "sentence": "8. \"In page 6, what is meant by 'more perceptually similar to the datapoint'?\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 25, "sentence": "We mean that the minimal adversarial distortion for models on CIFAR-10 is known to typically be much smaller than for MNIST."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 26, "sentence": "The result of this is that an adversarial example on MNIST will often have visual salt-and-pepper noise, whereas an adversarial example for CIFAR-10 typically is indistinguishable to the naked eye from its unperturbed datapoint."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 27, "sentence": "9. \"In the appendix: the MH acronym should better be introduced, as should the notation"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 28, "sentence": "g(x,|x')"}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 29, "sentence": "if not done elsewhere (in which case a cross-reference would be welcome)."}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 30, "sentence": "Besides this, writing \"the last samples\" requires disambiguation (using \"respective\"?).\""}, {"text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 31, "sentence": "We have added to this description so that it is less terse and more carefully introduces the notation, including changing \u201clast samples\u201d to \u201cfinal samples\u201d and adding in a reference for further reading."}], "rebuttallabels": [{"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "social", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 0}, {"labels": {"alignments": [8, 9], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 1}, {"labels": {"alignments": [8, 9], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "SkxO_sApa7", "sid": 2}, {"labels": {"alignments": [8, 9], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": 